name: life-events-ng
version: "1.0.0"
description: >
  Detailed Meta Ads life events targeting rules for Nigerian/West African SMEs. 
  Only load this skill when the campaign type is detected as life-stage relevant 
  (e.g., bridal, baby, home, corporate wear, gifts).
---

# Sellam Life Events Targeting Strategy (Nigeria)

Life Events are **separate from behaviors** — they go into the `life_events` field in the Meta API.
They target people at a specific moment in their life, not a general interest pattern.
Only include when the product or the user's described audience is **directly tied to that life stage**.

---

### Detection — Run All 3 Layers Silently

Work through these layers in order. Stop at the first layer that fires.

---

#### LAYER 1 — Explicit Audience Signals (Highest Priority)

The user directly describes their target audience's life stage.
These override product category inference. Always include the matched life event.

| User Says (English)                                                | Life Event                  |
| ------------------------------------------------------------------ | --------------------------- |
| "targeting brides" / "for brides-to-be" / "engaged women"          | Newly engaged (1 year)      |
| "for pregnant women" / "maternity customers" / "expecting mothers" | Expecting parents           |
| "for new moms" / "new parents" / "baby shower gifts"               | New parents (1 year)        |
| "people who just moved" / "housewarming" / "new apartment"         | Recently moved (6 months)   |
| "people in their new home" / "first home buyers"                   | New homeowner (1 year)      |
| "people starting a new job" / "for fresh graduates" / "NYSC"       | New job (6 months)          |
| "newly married couples" / "newlyweds" / "for honeymoon"            | Newly married (1 year)      |
| "people in new relationships" / "for Valentine's"                  | New relationship (6 months) |

**NYSC note:** National Youth Service Corps completion = start of career in Nigeria.
"NYSC corpers", "fresh corpers", "post-NYSC" → New job (6 months).

| User Says (Pidgin)                                               | Life Event                                                                  |
| ---------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| "mama wey just born" / "new mama"                                | New parents (1 year)                                                        |
| "couple wey just wed" / "dem just do wedding"                    | Newly married (1 year)                                                      |
| "she just do introduction" / "dem do introduction"               | Newly engaged (1 year) — "introduction" = traditional engagement in Nigeria |
| "babe wey just move enter new house" / "dem just enter new flat" | Recently moved (6 months)                                                   |
| "person wey just get work" / "e just start new work"             | New job (6 months)                                                          |
| "dem dey plan naming ceremony" / "baby naming"                   | New parents (1 year)                                                        |
| "bridal shower" / "hen night"                                    | Newly engaged (1 year)                                                      |
| "send-forth party"                                               | New job (6 months) — send-forth = farewell before new role                  |
| "housewarming" / "dem just pack in"                              | New homeowner (1 year)                                                      |

---

#### LAYER 2 — Occasion / Event Keywords

The user mentions an occasion that implies a life stage, even if they don't name the audience explicitly.

| Occasion Keyword                                        | Life Event             |
| ------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------- |
| "bridal shower", "bachelorette"                         | Newly engaged (1 year) |
| "baby naming", "naming ceremony", "1-year-old birthday" | New parents (1 year)   |
| "housewarming", "housewarming gift"                     | New homeowner (1 year) |
| "engagement party", "introduction party"                | Newly engaged (1 year) |
| "send-forth", "farewell party"                          | New job (6 months)     |
| "welcome back" (from NYSC/school)                       | New job (6 months)     |
| "newlywed gift", "wedding gift", "couple gift"          | Newly married (1 year) |
| "push present", "maternity gift"                        | Expecting parents      |

---

#### LAYER 3 — Product Category Inference

No explicit audience or occasion keyword found. Infer from what is being sold.

| Product / Business Type                                   | Life Event                                      | Confidence                                      |
| --------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
| Wedding dresses, bridal gowns, bridal accessories         | Newly engaged (1 year)                          | Strong                                          |
| Asoebi, aso-ebi fabric, aso-oke for weddings              | Newly engaged (1 year)                          | Strong                                          |
| Wedding catering, wedding photography, wedding decoration | Newly engaged (1 year)                          | Strong                                          |
| Wedding cakes, engagement cakes                           | Newly engaged (1 year)                          | Strong                                          |
| Baby clothes, baby products, diapers, baby accessories    | Expecting parents + New parents (1 year)        | Strong                                          |
| Maternity wear, antenatal products, nursing bras          | Expecting parents                               | Strong                                          |
| Cribs, prams, baby furniture                              | Expecting parents + New parents (1 year)        | Strong                                          |
| Home furniture, sofas, beds, wardrobes                    | New homeowner (1 year)                          | Strong                                          |
| Interior design services                                  | New homeowner (1 year)                          | Strong                                          |
| Kitchen appliances, cookware                              | New homeowner (1 year) + Newly married (1 year) | Strong                                          |
| Curtains, bedding, rugs, home decor                       | New homeowner (1 year)                          | Strong                                          |
| Moving / relocation services                              | Recently moved (6 months)                       | Strong                                          |
| Corporate wear, suits, office shirts                      | New job (6 months)                              | Strong                                          |
| Office shoes, professional bags, laptop bags              | New job (6 months)                              | Medium                                          |
| Grooming kits, perfume (professional angle)               | New job (6 months)                              | Medium — only if copy angle is "starting fresh" |
| Couple accessories, matching outfits                      | Newly married (1 year)                          | Medium                                          |
| Skincare (premium, anti-aging)                            | New relationship (6 months)                     | Weak — only include if other signals support it |
| Jewellery (engagement rings, bridal)                      | Newly engaged (1 year)                          | Strong                                          |
| Jewellery (general)                                       | New relationship (6 months)                     | Weak                                            |

**Confidence rules:**

- **Strong** → always include
- **Medium** → include only if the product description or copy angle supports it
- **Weak** → skip unless the user explicitly mentioned the relationship/occasion angle

---

### Never Include Life Events For These

These categories may seem adjacent but have no reliable life-stage connection.
Even if the user mentions weddings or babies in passing, do not add life events unless the _product itself_ serves that life stage.

- Food, restaurants, shawarma, buka, catering (general — not wedding-specific)
- Phone accessories, gadgets, electronics
- Generic fashion (Ankara bags, clutches, everyday clothing)
- Hair and wigs (general — not bridal hair specifically)
- Logistics, delivery services
- Financial services, loans
- Entertainment, events (general concerts, parties)
- Betting, gaming
- Digital products, courses, coaching (unless explicitly "career change" framing)

---

### Rules

1. **Maximum 2 life events per campaign** — precision beats volume
2. **Layer 1 and 2 always win over Layer 3** — explicit beats inferred
3. **Never stack weak signals** — if confidence is Weak, skip it
4. **Always LOG the exact life event in `meta.inferred_assumptions`** — e.g. "Triggered Life Event: Newly engaged (1 year) (Layer 3 - Strong)"
5. **Always mention life events in `reasoning`** — e.g. "Added Newly engaged because user sells wedding gowns — brides are the primary buyer at engagement stage"
6. **Return in `lifeEvents` array in output schema** — names must match exactly as they appear in Meta Ads Manager (see examples below)
7. **Empty array is valid** — most campaigns have no life events; do not force one

---

### Output Format

Return life event names exactly as they appear in Meta — the API resolves by name, not ID:

```json
"lifeEvents": [
  "Newly engaged (1 year)",
  "New parents (1 year)"
]
```

Empty when not applicable:

```json
"lifeEvents": []
```

---

### Full Examples

| Input                                            | Life Events Output                              | Layer Used                                |
| ------------------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| "I sell wedding gowns in Lagos"                  | `["Newly engaged (1 year)"]`                    | Layer 3 (Strong)                          |
| "We do bridal makeup and photography"            | `["Newly engaged (1 year)"]`                    | Layer 3 (Strong)                          |
| "Baby clothes and accessories Abuja"             | `["Expecting parents", "New parents (1 year)"]` | Layer 3 (Strong)                          |
| "Interior design services Lekki"                 | `["New homeowner (1 year)"]`                    | Layer 3 (Strong)                          |
| "Suits and corporate wear for men"               | `["New job (6 months)"]`                        | Layer 3 (Strong)                          |
| "Gifts for people wey just born pikin"           | `["New parents (1 year)"]`                      | Layer 1 (Pidgin)                          |
| "She just do introduction, I need asoebi fabric" | `["Newly engaged (1 year)"]`                    | Layer 1 (Pidgin — introduction)           |
| "Housewarming gift ideas, affordable"            | `["New homeowner (1 year)"]`                    | Layer 2 (Occasion)                        |
| "Send-forth party supplies and decor"            | `["New job (6 months)"]`                        | Layer 2 (Occasion)                        |
| "Baby naming decorations and small chops"        | `["New parents (1 year)"]`                      | Layer 2 (Occasion)                        |
| "NYSC corpers fashion — affordable and sharp"    | `["New job (6 months)"]`                        | Layer 1 (NYSC signal)                     |
| "I sell shawarma in Lekki"                       | `[]`                                            | None — food, no life stage                |
| "Ankara bags and clutches"                       | `[]`                                            | None — generic fashion                    |
| "Hair wigs, different colours"                   | `[]`                                            | None — general hair, not bridal-specific  |
| "Skincare for glowing skin"                      | `[]`                                            | None — Weak signal, no supporting context |
